[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/feos 
		"feos
	]a
	": Flash games can act weird if you randomly change resolution, especially if that breaks the game's native aspect ratio, because then you can click off-screen. That may need an extra discussion. But for movies that don't change aspect ratio, upscaling may result in a better look, because vector graphics will be able to use bigger internal resolution, which this run is doing. So while the native resolution movie is still the most legitimate, because it obeys original browser environment, higher resolution only requires slightly different mouse positioning (once in this case), and all the rest is the same, so it would be the most fair to have the hires run as a 
	[b 
		"secondary movie file
	]b
	" in the publication. 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Here it is|href=/UserFiles/Info/638062636148320617)
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Replacing the submission with the native res movie and accepting.
